  "narrative_arc": "Nigerian woman navigating American immigration, race, and class. Adichie documents the practical mechanics of immigrant survival — expired visas, borrowed Social Security numbers, the hair salon economy, the discovery that she is \"Black\" in America in a way she never was in Nigeria.",
  "why_this_character_matters": "Ifemelu's dome maps how race is a system, not just an identity. Her Layer 1 (Legal — immigration status) and Layer 8 (Community — racial classification) are completely reconfigured by crossing a border. Building her dome with real Philadelphia systems reveals the immigrant experience at ground level.",
